<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="499" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,1409,1869]" pageId="12" pageNumber="499">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1770,1796]" pageId="12" pageNumber="499">Remarks.</emphasis>
The species is widely distributed and was recorded in 
<collectingRegion box="[958,1114,1770,1796]" country="Brazil" name="Minas Gerais" pageId="12" pageNumber="499">Minas Gerais</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[1128,1365,1770,1796]" country="Brazil" name="Mato Grosso do Sul" pageId="12" pageNumber="499">Mato Grosso do Sul</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[1379,1432,1770,1796]" country="Brazil" name="Para" pageId="12" pageNumber="499">Pará</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[151,263,1806,1832]" country="Brazil" name="Rondonia" pageId="12" pageNumber="499">Rondônia</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[273,388,1806,1832]" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="12" pageNumber="499">São Paulo</collectingRegion>
, and 
<collectingRegion box="[444,552,1806,1832]" country="Brazil" name="Tocantins" pageId="12" pageNumber="499">Tocantins</collectingRegion>
states. It is the first record in 
<collectingRegion box="[879,1005,1806,1832]" country="Brazil" name="Goias" pageId="12" pageNumber="499">Goiás state</collectingRegion>
. The species has a characteristic penial armature (
<bibRefCitation author="Righi-Cavallaro, K. O. &amp; Lecci, L. S." box="[265,612,1842,1868]" pageId="12" pageNumber="499" pagination="35 - 44" refId="ref10222" refString="Righi-Cavallaro, K. O. &amp; Lecci, L. S. (2010) Three new species of Anacroneuria (Plecoptera: Perlidae) from Centre-West and Southeast Brazil. Zootaxa, 2683 (1), 35 - 44. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 2683.1.3" type="journal article" year="2010">Righi-Cavallaro &amp; Lecci 2010</bibRefCitation>
), and the nymph was originally described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Ribeiro, J. M. F. &amp; Gorayeb, I. S. &amp; Bispo, P. C." box="[1121,1353,1842,1869]" pageId="12" pageNumber="499" pagination="295 - 300" refId="ref10149" refString="Ribeiro, J. M. F., Gorayeb, I. S. &amp; Bispo, P. C. (2015) Description of the nymph of Anacroneuria singularis Righi-Cavallaro &amp; Lecci (Plecoptera: Perlidae) and a new locality record for northern Brazil. Zootaxa, 4057 (2), 295 - 300. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4057.2.11." type="journal article" year="2015">
Ribeiro 
<emphasis box="[1212,1261,1842,1868]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="499">et al</emphasis>
. (2015)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
